figo — design-systems/
==========================

This directory vendors design knowledge (design-system token sets and design
process skills) from the Open Design project:

    Open Design — https://github.com/nexu-io/open-design
    Copyright (c) Nexu, Inc. and the Open Design contributors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE-APACHE-2.0.txt).

What was taken (a curated subset, not the whole project):
  - design-systems/<name>/{DESIGN.md, design-tokens.json, tokens.css, USAGE.md}
    for 12 systems (linear-app, stripe, apple, notion, spotify, coinbase,
    revolut, duolingo, airbnb, material, neobrutalism, framer).
  - skills/{design-review, apple-hig, color-expert, brand-guidelines}.

What was NOT taken: the upstream HTML/CSS/GSAP artifacts, plugins, and the
Next.js/Electron application — figo renders Figma nodes through ThorVG, not
a browser, so those runtime pieces do not apply here.

Modifications by figo (per Apache-2.0 §4.b, "carry prominent notices"):
  - Files copied verbatim; no edits to the upstream DESIGN.md / *.json content.
  - README.md and TOKEN_MAPPING.md in this directory are original figo work
    that adapts the upstream token schema to figo's figoedit MCP pipeline.

Some skills are themselves curated from third parties; their own upstreams are
recorded in each skill's SKILL.md frontmatter (e.g. design-review is curated
from gstack by Garry Tan, https://github.com/garrytan/gstack).

Separately vendored (NOT from Open Design, different license):
  - skills/taste/ — an "anti-slop frontend" design-taste skill, vendored from
    taste-skill (https://github.com/Leonxlnx/taste-skill), Copyright (c) 2026
    Leonxlnx, MIT License (see skills/taste/LICENSE). A curated subset of the
    upstream skills/ tree: the comprehensive main skill plus the portable
    minimalist / soft / brutalist / redesign aesthetic variants, copied
    verbatim. NOT taken: the upstream image-to-code / imagegen / brandkit /
    stitch / gpt / output skills and the React/HTML/GSAP runtime pieces — figo
    renders Figma nodes through ThorVG, not a browser. The framework-agnostic
    taste principles are adapted to figo's figoedit MCP pipeline by the
    .claude/skills/figo-design skill; see skills/taste/SOURCE.md.
